# Metadata for chapter-10.md

## Provenance
- **Status:** POSTHUMOUS RECONSTRUCTION -- not written by Xavier O. Monasterio
- **Drafted:** 2026-07-04, with AI assistance (Claude), curated by Jorge Monasterio
- **No original source file exists.** Xavier's manuscript ends with chapter 8, whose final pages are working notes.

## Sources used for reconstruction
- NARRATIV (1990) -- primacy of consent over assent; Clamence (Camus, The Fall) vs. Abraham; "Assent and Consent" quoted therein
- REVELAT (1990) -- faith as consent, ob-audire, "Scio cui credidi", "Se en manos de quien estoy"
- chapter-5.md -- the Fathers' credere in Deum / credere Deo / credere Deum
- chapter-8.md working notes -- practical comprehension vs. cognitive interpretation

## Classification
- **Type:** Reconstructed book manuscript chapter (chapter 10 of projected continuation)
- **Part of:** Unpublished book on philosophy of religion

## Notes
This chapter attempts to complete the book's argument as Xavier outlined it in his own
notes and parallel essays, in his voice. It should not be quoted or cited as his writing.
